MODULE: src/services
FILES: 30
RESPONSIBILITY: Core service layer — AI CLI execution, session management, messaging, pipeline control, monitoring
INTERFACES:
- executeAiCli(options): Promise<AiCliExecutionResult> — unified AI CLI executor with process tracking
- interruptAiCli(sessionId): {ok, pid?, error?} — interrupt running AI task
- createMessageRouter({aiCliExecutor, sessionStore, realtimeHub}): MessageRouter — F-018 unified message processor
- processMessage({channel, sessionId, message, telegramChatId?, userId?, hooks?}): Promise<{reply}> — route message through AI CLI
- createSessionBindService({bindingsPath}): SessionBindingService — F-018 factory with deferred init
- SessionBindingService.bindSession(webId, chatId): {ok} — bind web session to Telegram chat
- SessionBindingService.getBoundChatId(webId): string|null — lookup binding
- SessionBindingService.getBoundWebSessions(chatId): string[] — reverse lookup
- SessionBindingService.ensureReady(): Promise<void> — wait for deferred init
- sessionStore.append(key, role, content) — append message to session
- sessionStore.toPrompt(key, channel): string — build prompt with context
- realtimeHub.subscribe(key, listener): unsubscribe — SSE event pub/sub
- realtimeHub.publish(key, event) — broadcast event to subscribers
- chatWithSession({channel, sessionId, message, realtimeHooks}): Promise<reply> — legacy Web chat (deprecated by F-018)
DEPENDENCIES:
- uses: node:child_process: spawn for AI CLI process
- uses: zod: config validation
- uses: node:fs/promises: session persistence, bindings file
- imports: src/config.js: runtime configuration
- imports: src/security/guard.js: sanitizeInput
KEY_FILES:
- ai-cli-service.js: AI CLI executor with heartbeat, timeout, metrics (564 lines)
- message-router.js: F-018 unified message processor (128 lines)
- session-bind.js: F-018 session binding with persistence (~220 lines)
- session-store.js: in-memory session state (427 lines)
- realtime-hub.js: SSE event pub/sub (35 lines)
- chat-service.js: legacy chat via codebuddy adapter (80 lines, deprecated)
TRAPS:
- SessionBindingService uses deferred init — always call ensureReady() before sync methods in async contexts
- SessionBindingService persistence is fire-and-forget — tests must call flush() to verify file writes
- messageRouter does not expose heartbeat hooks — Telegram heartbeat progress disabled after F-018 migration
- Runtime bindings created via POST /api/bind do NOT auto-subscribe realtimeHub for cross-channel push (F-018 gap)
UPDATED: 2026-03-22
